        "subject": "LU-1114 ptlrpc: synchronize ptlrpcd partner threads at start",
        "message": "LU-1114 ptlrpc: synchronize ptlrpcd partner threads at start\n\nThe ptlrpcd threads can take some work from their partner threads,\nsee ptlrpcd_check() routine. However, the start of all the ptlrcpd\nthreads is not synchronized wich can lead to access the ptlrcpd_ctl\nstructure of a partner thread that has not been initialized.\n\nThis patch ensures partner thread control structure is accessed\nonly when it is completely initialized.\n\nSigned-off-by: Gregoire Pichon <gregoire.pichon@bull.net>\nChange-Id: Ie24f28103fa65120f77d22b4c5debae149c451b4\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
